<emphasis box="[481,646,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. chalcedona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the rusty-brown area from the antemedial line to the outer wing margin and the presence of the dark dash in the apical white area of the forewing. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[276,366,404,429]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[276,366,404,429]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ clearly from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Cerny" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[684,845,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcedona">
<emphasis box="[684,845,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. chalcedona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the significantly smaller, poorly developed apical costal lobe, the absence of a basal dentation of the costa, the nuch smaller distal membranous lobe of the valve, and the slightly smaller spines on the distal diverticulum of the aedeagus vesica. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[1245,1396,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1245,1396,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="23" pageNumber="424" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
also resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[475,574,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diehli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[475,574,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. diehli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[583,675,511,536]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[583,675,511,536]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but can be distinguished in the broader valve, the less developed medial costal angle, the significantly smaller apical costal lobe, the broader ventral costal plate, the significantly shorter ampulla, which is lobe-like, and has two small dens on its ventral surface (whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[1207,1304,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diehli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1207,1304,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. diehli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1312,1402,583,608]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1312,1402,583,608]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the ampulla is elongated, trigonal), the slightly longer subapical saccular process, the significantly longer and narrower aedeagus, the larger and more heavily sclerotized carinal plate, the much narrower medial and distal diverticula of the vesica, and the ansence of a subbasal diverticulum. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[1053,1204,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1053,1204,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1213,1304,692,717]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1213,1304,692,717]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Cerny" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[252,415,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcedona">
<emphasis box="[252,415,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">N. chalcedona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shorter and significantly broader antevaginal plate, the broader ostium bursae, the slightly broader ductus bursae, the broader cluster of spinules in the medial section of the corpus bursae, and the slightly smaller signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,805,836,861]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,805,836,861]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,836,861]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Distribution</emphasis>
. Endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[494,587,836,860]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
Island (
<collectingCountry box="[678,793,836,861]" name="Indonesia" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="424" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,871,896]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Etymology</emphasis>
. ‘Ferrugineus’ is ‘ferruginous’ in Latin, the species name refers to its rusty-brown forewing coloration.
</paragraph>
